1. Project Title

Student Course Enrollment System using Java Collections

2. Problem Statement

To design and implement a Student Course Enrollment System that allows users to enter student details, enroll in courses, and display enrolled students. The system should efficiently store and manage student records using Java collections.

3. Objective
To create a student enrollment system using Java.
To store student data using collections (ArrayList).
To perform enrollment and display operations.
To improve logical thinking and programming skills.
To understand data management using collections.
4. Tools Used
Java (JDK)
VS Code / Eclipse / IntelliJ IDEA
5. Description

This project implements a Student Course Enrollment System using Java. The system allows users to enter student names and course details through a console-based interface. Student records are stored dynamically using an ArrayList, which enables efficient data storage and retrieval. Users can add students, view enrolled students, and manage enrollment records through a simple menu-driven program.

6. Algorithm
Start the program.
Create an empty ArrayList to store student records.
Display menu options.
Read the user's choice.
If Add Student is selected, enter student name and course details.
Store the student record in the ArrayList.
If Display Students is selected, show all enrolled students.
Repeat the process until Exit is selected.
End the program.
7. Program

Java program to manage student course enrollment using ArrayList.

8. Sample Output

The program displays a menu that allows users to add student records, view enrolled students, and exit the application. Enrolled student details are displayed in a structured format.

9. Result

The Student Course Enrollment System was successfully developed using Java collections. The program allows users to add and display student enrollment records efficiently using ArrayList.

10. Conclusion

This project demonstrates the use of Java collections for managing student enrollment data. It helps in understanding object-oriented programming concepts, collections, loops, conditional statements, and user input handling. The system provides an efficient way to store and display student enrollment records in a console-based environment.
